-> For Classes , Structs and enum , use PascalCase 
-> For functions and variables , use camelCase.
-> Always put { and } on new lines.
-> Use spaces around binary operators, after commas in function arguments, and between control flow statements and parentheses.
-> For constants , use UpperCase . 
-> Use // for single-line comments.
-> Use /* */ only for blocks or disabling code.
-> Use braces even for single-line bodies.
-> Always initialize variables to prevent undefined behavior.
-> Minimize the use of global variables . 